{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1286,"text":"In this talk today, I want to present a different idea"},{"time":5774,"text":"for why investing in early childhood education"},{"time":9995,"text":"makes sense as a public investment."},{"time":12694,"text":"It's a different idea, because usually,"},{"time":14932,"text":"when people talk about early childhood programs,"},{"time":16305,"text":"they talk about all the wonderful benefits for participants"},{"time":19646,"text":"in terms of former participants, in preschool,"},{"time":22928,"text":"they have better K-12 test scores,"},{"time":25193,"text":"better adult earnings."},{"time":27308,"text":"Now that's all very important,"},{"time":29423,"text":"but what I want to talk about is what preschool does"},{"time":33519,"text":"for state economies"},{"time":35341,"text":"and for promoting state economic development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38638,"text":"And that's actually crucial"},{"time":41931,"text":"because if we're going to get increased investment"},{"time":45255,"text":"in early childhood programs,"},{"time":47598,"text":"we need to interest state governments in this."},{"time":51121,"text":"The federal government has a lot on its plate,"},{"time":53347,"text":"and state governments are going to have to step up."},{"time":55845,"text":"So we have to appeal to them,"},{"time":58028,"text":"the legislators in the state government,"},{"time":60581,"text":"and turn to something they understand,"},{"time":62571,"text":"that they have to promote the economic development"},{"time":64869,"text":"of their state economy."},{"time":66556,"text":"Now, by promoting economic development,"},{"time":68372,"text":"I don't mean anything magical."},{"time":70086,"text":"All I mean is, is that early childhood education"},{"time":73549,"text":"can bring more and better jobs to a state"},{"time":77452,"text":"and can thereby promote higher per capita earnings"},{"time":80630,"text":"for the state's residents."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82580,"text":"Now, I think it's fair to say that when people think about"},{"time":86573,"text":"state and local economic development,"},{"time":88577,"text":"they don't generally think first about what they're doing"},{"time":92359,"text":"about childcare and early childhood programs."},{"time":94914,"text":"I know this. I've spent most of my career researching these programs."},{"time":98817,"text":"I've talked to a lot of directors"},{"time":100440,"text":"of state economic development agencies about these issues,"},{"time":102768,"text":"a lot of legislators about these issues."},{"time":105310,"text":"When legislators and others think about economic development,"},{"time":108369,"text":"what they first of all think about are business tax incentives,"},{"time":111625,"text":"property tax abatements, job creation tax credits,"},{"time":114503,"text":"you know, there are a million of these programs all over the place."},{"time":117190,"text":"So for example, states compete very vigorously"},{"time":119796,"text":"to attract new auto plants or expanded auto plants."},{"time":123461,"text":"They hand out all kinds of business tax breaks."},{"time":125601,"text":"Now, those programs can make sense"},{"time":127799,"text":"if they in fact induce new location decisions,"},{"time":130801,"text":"and the way they can make sense is,"},{"time":132186,"text":"by creating more and better jobs,"},{"time":134499,"text":"they raise employment rates, raise per capita earnings of state residents."},{"time":138082,"text":"So there is a benefit to state residents"},{"time":140152,"text":"that corresponds to the costs that they're paying"},{"time":142301,"text":"by paying for these business tax breaks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144574,"text":"My argument is essentially that early childhood programs"},{"time":148382,"text":"can do exactly the same thing,"},{"time":152107,"text":"create more and better jobs, but in a different way."},{"time":156016,"text":"It's a somewhat more indirect way."},{"time":158434,"text":"These programs can promote more and better jobs by,"},{"time":162080,"text":"you build it, you invest in high-quality preschool,"},{"time":164955,"text":"it develops the skills of your local workforce"},{"time":168773,"text":"if enough of them stick around, and, in turn,"},{"time":172516,"text":"that higher-quality local workforce"},{"time":174669,"text":"will be a key driver of creating jobs and creating"},{"time":179361,"text":"higher earnings per capita in the local community."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181869,"text":"Now, let me turn to some numbers on this."},{"time":184833,"text":"Okay. If you look at the research evidence --"},{"time":189416,"text":"that's extensive -- on how much early childhood programs"},{"time":194079,"text":"affect the educational attainment, wages and skills"},{"time":198676,"text":"of former participants in preschool as adults,"},{"time":202185,"text":"you take those known effects,"},{"time":204821,"text":"you take how many of those folks will be expected"},{"time":207509,"text":"to stick around the state or local economy and not move out,"},{"time":211210,"text":"and you take research on how much skills"},{"time":215030,"text":"drive job creation, you will conclude,"},{"time":218201,"text":"from these three separate lines of research,"},{"time":220244,"text":"that for every dollar invested in early childhood programs,"},{"time":224323,"text":"the per capita earnings of state residents"},{"time":227776,"text":"go up by two dollars and 78 cents,"},{"time":230542,"text":"so that's a three-to-one return."},{"time":232409,"text":"Now you can get much higher returns,"},{"time":235442,"text":"of up to 16-to-one, if you include anti-crime benefits,"},{"time":239516,"text":"if you include benefits to former preschool participants"},{"time":244230,"text":"who move to some other state,"},{"time":246414,"text":"but there's a good reason for focusing on these three dollars"},{"time":249425,"text":"because this is salient and important"},{"time":251512,"text":"to state legislators and state policy makers,"},{"time":253802,"text":"and it's the states that are going to have to act."},{"time":255946,"text":"So there is this key benefit that is relevant"},{"time":259245,"text":"to state policy makers in terms of economic development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262494,"text":"Now, one objection you often hear,"},{"time":265912,"text":"or maybe you don't hear it because people are too polite to say it, is,"},{"time":270809,"text":"why should I pay more taxes"},{"time":275272,"text":"to invest in other people's children?"},{"time":279550,"text":"What's in it for me?"},{"time":282044,"text":"And the trouble with that objection,"},{"time":284323,"text":"it reflects a total misunderstanding"},{"time":288325,"text":"of how much local economies"},{"time":291342,"text":"involve everyone being interdependent."},{"time":294848,"text":"Specifically, the interdependency here is, is that"},{"time":298765,"text":"there are huge spillovers of skills --"},{"time":302298,"text":"that when other people's children get more skills,"},{"time":307618,"text":"that actually increases the prosperity of everyone,"},{"time":311387,"text":"including people whose skills don't change."},{"time":314741,"text":"So for example, numerous research studies have shown"},{"time":317145,"text":"if you look at what really drives"},{"time":319724,"text":"the growth rate of metropolitan areas,"},{"time":322188,"text":"it's not so much low taxes, low cost, low wages;"},{"time":327858,"text":"it's the skills of the area. Particularly, the proxy for skills"},{"time":331481,"text":"that people use is percentage of college graduates in the area."},{"time":335016,"text":"So when you look, for example, at metropolitan areas"},{"time":338095,"text":"such as the Boston area, Minneapolis-St. Paul,"},{"time":341608,"text":"Silicon Valley, these areas are not doing well economically"},{"time":346944,"text":"because they're low-cost."},{"time":349253,"text":"I don't know if you ever tried to buy a house in Silicon Valley."},{"time":351178,"text":"It's not exactly a low-cost proposition."},{"time":353995,"text":"They are growing because they have high levels of skills."},{"time":359940,"text":"So when we invest in other people's children,"},{"time":363095,"text":"and build up those skills, we increase the overall job growth"},{"time":367280,"text":"of a metro area."},{"time":368801,"text":"As another example, if we look"},{"time":372689,"text":"at what determines an individual's wages,"},{"time":375924,"text":"and we do statistical exploration of that, what determines wages,"},{"time":380149,"text":"we know that the individual's wages will depend, in part,"},{"time":384672,"text":"on that individual's education,"},{"time":387103,"text":"for example whether or not they have a college degree."},{"time":390096,"text":"One of the very interesting facts is that, in addition,"},{"time":393434,"text":"we find that even once we hold constant, statistically,"},{"time":397481,"text":"the effect of your own education,"},{"time":400385,"text":"the education of everyone else in your metropolitan area"},{"time":403585,"text":"also affects your wages."},{"time":405557,"text":"So specifically, if you hold constant your education,"},{"time":409761,"text":"you stick in percentage of college graduates in your metro area,"},{"time":413864,"text":"you will find that has a significant positive effect on your wages"},{"time":417824,"text":"without changing your education at all."},{"time":421294,"text":"In fact, this effect is so strong"},{"time":424445,"text":"that when someone gets a college degree,"},{"time":428258,"text":"the spillover effects of this on the wages"},{"time":430699,"text":"of others in the metropolitan area"},{"time":432592,"text":"are actually greater than the direct effects."},{"time":435694,"text":"So if someone gets a college degree, their lifetime earnings"},{"time":439147,"text":"go up by a huge amount, over 700,000 dollars."},{"time":442462,"text":"There's an effect on everyone else in the metro area"},{"time":444977,"text":"of driving up the percentage of college graduates in the metro area,"},{"time":448840,"text":"and if you add that up -- it's a small effect for each person,"},{"time":452256,"text":"but if you add that up across all the people in the metro area,"},{"time":455688,"text":"you actually get that the increase in wages for everyone else"},{"time":459314,"text":"in the metropolitan area adds up to almost a million dollars."},{"time":462227,"text":"That's actually greater than the direct benefits"},{"time":464305,"text":"of the person choosing to get education."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467359,"text":"Now, what's going on here?"},{"time":468718,"text":"What can explain these huge spillover effects of education?"},{"time":472641,"text":"Well, let's think about it this way."},{"time":474115,"text":"I can be the most skilled person in the world,"},{"time":477438,"text":"but if everyone else at my firm lacks skills,"},{"time":481239,"text":"my employer is going to find it more difficult"},{"time":484208,"text":"to introduce new technology, new production techniques."},{"time":488264,"text":"So as a result, my employer is going to be less productive."},{"time":491866,"text":"They will not be able to afford to pay me as good wages."},{"time":495467,"text":"Even if everyone at my firm has good skills,"},{"time":499148,"text":"if the workers at the suppliers to my firm"},{"time":502656,"text":"do not have good skills,"},{"time":504626,"text":"my firm is going to be less competitive"},{"time":507023,"text":"competing in national and international markets."},{"time":509408,"text":"And again, the firm that's less competitive"},{"time":512502,"text":"will not be able to pay as good wages,"},{"time":515191,"text":"and then, particularly in high-tech businesses,"},{"time":519324,"text":"they're constantly stealing ideas and workers from other businesses."},{"time":522585,"text":"So clearly the productivity of firms in Silicon Valley"},{"time":525805,"text":"has a lot to do with the skills not only of the workers at their firm,"},{"time":529600,"text":"but the workers at all the other firms in the metro area."},{"time":534019,"text":"So as a result, if we can invest in other people's children"},{"time":537553,"text":"through preschool and other early childhood programs"},{"time":539955,"text":"that are high-quality, we not only help those children,"},{"time":543611,"text":"we help everyone in the metropolitan area"},{"time":547232,"text":"gain in wages and we'll have the metropolitan area"},{"time":550903,"text":"gain in job growth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552925,"text":"Another objection used sometimes here"},{"time":555456,"text":"to invest in early childhood programs"},{"time":557684,"text":"is concern about people moving out."},{"time":561405,"text":"So, you know, maybe Ohio's thinking about investing"},{"time":565640,"text":"in more preschool education"},{"time":567884,"text":"for children in Columbus, Ohio,"},{"time":571694,"text":"but they're worried that these little Buckeyes will,"},{"time":573953,"text":"for some strange reason, decide to move to Ann Arbor, Michigan,"},{"time":576870,"text":"and become Wolverines."},{"time":578387,"text":"And maybe Michigan will be thinking about investing"},{"time":581681,"text":"in preschool in Ann Arbor, Michigan, and be worried"},{"time":584122,"text":"these little Wolverines will end up moving to Ohio and becoming Buckeyes."},{"time":587357,"text":"And so they'll both underinvest because everyone's going to move out."},{"time":591349,"text":"Well, the reality is, if you look at the data,"},{"time":594290,"text":"Americans aren't as hyper-mobile as people sometimes assume."},{"time":598503,"text":"The data is that over 60 percent of Americans"},{"time":603623,"text":"spend most of their working careers"},{"time":606061,"text":"in the state they were born in, over 60 percent."},{"time":609831,"text":"That percentage does not vary much from state to state."},{"time":613926,"text":"It doesn't vary much with the state's economy,"},{"time":617030,"text":"whether it's depressed or booming,"},{"time":618828,"text":"it doesn't vary much over time."},{"time":621149,"text":"So the reality is, if you invest in kids,"},{"time":626962,"text":"they will stay."},{"time":629461,"text":"Or at least, enough of them will stay"},{"time":632499,"text":"that it will pay off for your state economy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635920,"text":"Okay, so to sum up, there is a lot of research evidence"},{"time":639844,"text":"that early childhood programs, if run in a high-quality way,"},{"time":642998,"text":"pay off in higher adult skills."},{"time":645854,"text":"There's a lot of research evidence"},{"time":647421,"text":"that those folks will stick around the state economy,"},{"time":651045,"text":"and there's a lot of evidence that having more workers"},{"time":654362,"text":"with higher skills in your local economy"},{"time":656452,"text":"pays off in higher wages and job growth for your local economy,"},{"time":660131,"text":"and if you calculate the numbers for each dollar,"},{"time":663574,"text":"we get about three dollars back"},{"time":666303,"text":"in benefits for the state economy."},{"time":668478,"text":"So in my opinion, the research evidence is compelling"},{"time":672090,"text":"and the logic of this is compelling."},{"time":674914,"text":"So what are the barriers to getting it done?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":678604,"text":"Well, one obvious barrier is cost."},{"time":681868,"text":"So if you look at what it would cost"},{"time":686198,"text":"if every state government invested"},{"time":689025,"text":"in universal preschool at age four, full-day preschool at age four,"},{"time":693230,"text":"the total annual national cost would be roughly"},{"time":696645,"text":"30 billion dollars."},{"time":698950,"text":"So, 30 billion dollars is a lot of money."},{"time":701375,"text":"On the other hand, if you reflect on"},{"time":705120,"text":"that the U.S.'s population is over 300 million,"},{"time":708980,"text":"we're talking about an amount of money"},{"time":711663,"text":"that amounts to 100 dollars per capita."},{"time":714283,"text":"Okay? A hundred dollars per capita, per person,"},{"time":717261,"text":"is something that any state government can afford to do."},{"time":721266,"text":"It's just a simple matter of political will to do it."},{"time":726015,"text":"And, of course, as I mentioned,"},{"time":727895,"text":"this cost has corresponding benefits."},{"time":730049,"text":"I mentioned there's a multiplier of about three,"},{"time":732225,"text":"2.78, for the state economy,"},{"time":734325,"text":"in terms of over 80 billion in extra earnings."},{"time":737354,"text":"And if we want to translate that from just billions of dollars"},{"time":740378,"text":"to something that might mean something,"},{"time":742271,"text":"what we're talking about is that, for the average low-income kid,"},{"time":745859,"text":"that would increase earnings by about 10 percent"},{"time":748976,"text":"over their whole career, just doing the preschool,"},{"time":752175,"text":"not improving K-12 or anything else after that,"},{"time":754690,"text":"not doing anything with college tuition or access,"},{"time":757238,"text":"just directly improving preschool,"},{"time":759934,"text":"and we would get five percent higher earnings"},{"time":762233,"text":"for middle-class kids."},{"time":763629,"text":"So this is an investment"},{"time":765694,"text":"that pays off in very concrete terms"},{"time":768602,"text":"for a broad range of income groups in the state's population"},{"time":773022,"text":"and produces large and tangible benefits."}]},{"cues":[{"time":777532,"text":"Now, that's one barrier."},{"time":780086,"text":"I actually think the more profound barrier"},{"time":783508,"text":"is the long-term nature of the benefits from early childhood programs."},{"time":787938,"text":"So the argument I'm making is, is that we're increasing"},{"time":790784,"text":"the quality of our local workforce,"},{"time":792539,"text":"and thereby increasing economic development."},{"time":795205,"text":"Obviously if we have a preschool with four-year-olds,"},{"time":798585,"text":"we're not sending these kids out at age five"},{"time":800953,"text":"to work in the sweatshops, right? At least I hope not."},{"time":804468,"text":"So we're talking about an investment"},{"time":807880,"text":"that in terms of impacts on the state economy"},{"time":810350,"text":"is not going to really pay off for 15 or 20 years,"},{"time":814311,"text":"and of course America is notorious for being"},{"time":817169,"text":"a short term-oriented society."},{"time":820176,"text":"Now one response you can make to this,"},{"time":821836,"text":"and I sometimes have done this in talks,"},{"time":823361,"text":"is people can talk about, there are benefits for these programs"},{"time":826438,"text":"in reducing special ed and remedial education costs,"},{"time":830085,"text":"there are benefits, parents care about preschool,"},{"time":832391,"text":"maybe we'll get some migration effects"},{"time":834641,"text":"from parents seeking good preschool,"},{"time":836959,"text":"and I think those are true,"},{"time":838606,"text":"but in some sense they're missing the point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":840768,"text":"Ultimately, this is something"},{"time":843339,"text":"we're investing in now for the future."},{"time":847264,"text":"And so what I want to leave you with is"},{"time":851213,"text":"what I think is the ultimate question."},{"time":853519,"text":"I mean, I'm an economist, but this is ultimately"},{"time":856353,"text":"not an economic question, it's a moral question:"},{"time":861898,"text":"Are we willing, as Americans,"},{"time":866105,"text":"are we as a society still capable"},{"time":869555,"text":"of making the political choice to sacrifice now"},{"time":874339,"text":"by paying more taxes"},{"time":876988,"text":"in order to improve the long-term future"},{"time":882193,"text":"of not only our kids, but our community?"},{"time":885610,"text":"Are we still capable of that as a country?"},{"time":890057,"text":"And that's something that each and every citizen"},{"time":892498,"text":"and voter needs to ask themselves."},{"time":895041,"text":"Is that something that you are still invested in,"},{"time":897986,"text":"that you still believe in the notion of investment?"},{"time":900720,"text":"That is the notion of investment."},{"time":902119,"text":"You sacrifice now for a return later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":904693,"text":"So I think the research evidence"},{"time":908331,"text":"on the benefits of early childhood programs"},{"time":910969,"text":"for the local economy is extremely strong."},{"time":914576,"text":"However, the moral and political choice"},{"time":918858,"text":"is still up to us, as citizens and as voters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":923962,"text":"Thank you very much. (Applause)"}]}]}